{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-tsx","path":"/radians/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Radian</h1>\n<p>A radian (<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">rad</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span>) is the angle (<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\theta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">θ</span></span></span></span>) which subtends an arc equal to the length of the radius of a <a href=\"../circles/\">circle</a> and the SI unit of angles. The angle of a circle is <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2\\pi</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span></span></span></span> radians.</p>\n<h2>Convert Between Radians and Degrees</h2>\n<p>Given there are <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>360</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">°</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">360\\degree</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mord\">6</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mord\">°</span></span></span></span> in a circle and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2\\pi\\ rad</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span> in a circle, we can say <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>360</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">°</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">360\\degree = 2\\pi\\ rad</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">3</span><span class=\"mord\">6</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mord\">°</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>You can solve for either side of the equation to determine the formula for conversion.</p>\n<p>First, simplify:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>180</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">°</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>π</mi><mtext> </mtext><mi>r</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">180\\degree = \\pi\\ rad</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mord\">8</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mord\">°</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.69444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">π</span><span class=\"mspace\"> </span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">r</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span></span></span></span></p>\n<h2>Video: Intro to Radians</h2>\n<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EnwWxMZVBeg\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<h2>Resources to Learn About Radians</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.khanacademy.org/math/algebra2/x2ec2f6f830c9fb89:trig/x2ec2f6f830c9fb89:radians/v/introduction-to-radians\">Intro to Radians on Khan Academy</a></li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/radians/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Radian","tags":["math","circles"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/radians/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2270328656","3794076007","80858887"]}